issue.title: False positives
issue.body: So IdenProf is great at distinguishing say, an image of a police officer from an image of a firefighter. Out of curiosity I tried getting it to predict the professions of images that do not fall into any of the 10 categories, expecting results with low probability/certainty. Unfortunately this was not the case. It tends to express a high level of certainty even when it shouldn't. ``` image: test_images\boxer.jpg waiter : 99.28185939788818 chef : 0.4938141442835331 doctor : 0.13351680245250463 ``` ``` image: test_images\cyclist.jpg police : 95.38164734840393 mechanic : 3.639966994524002 farmer : 0.9620786644518375 ``` ``` image: test_images\film_critic.jpg firefighter : 96.90539836883545 mechanic : 2.035141922533512 judge : 0.8867966011166573 ``` ``` image: test_images\food_critic.jpg judge : 64.44069743156433 waiter : 31.9767564535141 chef : 3.5824909806251526 ``` ``` image: test_images\person.jpg pilot : 82.74794816970825 doctor : 16.624705493450165 judge : 0.6167999934405088 ``` ``` image: test_images\person2.jpg waiter : 55.20762801170349 judge : 43.84030997753143 doctor : 0.8999278768897057 ``` ``` image: test_images\person3.jpg judge : 99.99868869781494 waiter : 0.0009612601388653275 farmer : 0.00032320690479537006 ``` ``` image: test_images\person4.jpg pilot : 96.692955493927 police : 2.24935095757246 farmer : 0.48480830155313015 ``` ``` image: test_images\person5.jpg pilot : 98.77968430519104 judge : 0.4517796915024519 police : 0.375298666767776 ``` ``` image: test_images\person6.jpg pilot : 99.83604550361633 engineer : 0.15157574089244008 doctor : 0.006174622831167653 ``` ``` image: test_images\person7.jpg mechanic : 56.29146695137024 farmer : 35.54711639881134 pilot : 6.040527299046516 ``` ``` image: test_images\photographer.jpg doctor : 87.44643330574036 police : 12.040632963180542 waiter : 0.23560849949717522 ``` ``` image: test_images\photographer2.jpg waiter : 64.6943986415863 doctor : 22.024451196193695 pilot : 6.768552213907242 ``` ``` image: test_images\programmer.jpg police : 72.09265232086182 mechanic : 25.71178674697876 judge : 1.56310573220253 ``` ``` image: test_images\stripper.jpg judge : 86.99167370796204 waiter : 12.583789229393005 mechanic : 0.265811407007277 ``` ``` image: test_images\writer.jpg doctor : 99.8594343662262 waiter : 0.13804479967802763 mechanic : 0.0012477327800297644 ``` What could be done to resolve this? Perhaps an `other` category, with the training data populated by images of "generic" people (or famous, but wearing regular clothing)?

issue.title: Detection of new professions
issue.body: I'm thinking of new professions to add to this project. Since professions can be dressed differently in different countries and cultures this is hard. But I think that a religious "leader" such a priests, pastor, father, imam, monk, bishop, preacher, rabbi are quite identifiable. Is there any interest in this? I could help collect those images.
